<subSubSection id="7D0229835E9E080CF6FDD2096AC65519" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="ECDF818354339616A38C27B8ACA4B4FD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="73B3BBF0095FF9C83FB827D7E59A6DEB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Almost endemic to the Chamela region in dry deciduous forest at low altitudes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A874C1452DF9EE06AABD3399703AFE5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="A0E52439A550773813E6E508F60D2BD5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">MEXICO. Guerrero</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="5B5E0DAD881F1593B8BB9F4D3BD01D32" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cortez &amp; Lozano</emphasis>
2621 (MEXU), fide McDonald (1987). 
<emphasis id="8C6550598820EA4B1ABB1567234FC53E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Jalisco</emphasis>
: Chamela, 
<emphasis id="654EE32687866E3F2A58D2455EB93520" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. Gentry &amp; L. Woodruff</emphasis>
74402 (FTG, MO); 
<emphasis id="A4453B4783CCBD2414586B9E3276D6E7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. Lott</emphasis>
1207 (MEXU, MO); 11 km S of Guadalajara, 
<emphasis id="21704184A891245E35D32EF36BF1C070" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. Harker &amp; H. Mellowes</emphasis>
91 (BM); 
<emphasis id="180BE8487C8898F53A5DC68664D54732" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<normalizedToken id="EE96EC6E2246526D877D8B19A81C1B6F" originalValue="Michoacán">Michoacan</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
: Aquila, Barranca de Chila, 
<emphasis id="9DB8BA649FADF4598F298A4D83B4BDDA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">J.C. Soto et al.</emphasis>
2621 (IEB).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="155314A07F335BE9252DEF192C1BCCAC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="EE161E77B8F70370F38ECC7979722612" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AADA00B0A5628F05CAE60015715170E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is distinguished by the white salverform corolla and 3-lobed leaves, but is otherwise very similar to 
<emphasis id="00A84AA8A3F5B507D1204B93930C221F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="2773FBF8DBA553DCB1DCDEB4575116D1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="proxima">Ipomoea proxima</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="629614E9056F8CC38D333007EB382851" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopulorum">I. scopulorum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
